CatDescriptText: Mr. "Al" Holt, janitor, Uptown, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 29, 1961, pg.7 with question: "Do you believe that Russia actually 'put a man in space'--in orbit around the earth, or do you think that it was a 'trial run' to test man and rocket, prior to an attempt to put him in actual orbit in outer space?" answer reads: "So far as I read this seems to be true."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of "Al" Holt wearing eyeglasses, hat, and plaid button down collared shirt
